.nh
.TH "BCDOCK" "1" "Jan 2025" "BCDock CLI" "BCDock Manual"

.SH NAME
bcdock-me-billing-checkout - Start a Stripe Checkout flow for a chosen tier+currency (prints the hosted URL)


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbcdock me billing checkout [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Creates a Stripe Checkout Session and prints the URL to open in a browser.
Stripe handles card collection, 3DS, Apple/Google Pay, then redirects back to the
portal /billing page. BCDock mirrors the new subscription server-side within
seconds of the customer completing the flow.

.PP
This is the only path for trial users to add a card and convert to a paid tier.
After conversion, use 'bcdock me billing portal' for ongoing card / plan management.

.PP
Exit codes:
  0   ok
  1   general error (invalid tier or currency)
  3   auth failure (missing or invalid token)
  4   rate-limited


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--cancel-url\fP=""
	URL Stripe redirects to if the user cancels (optional)

.PP
\fB--currency\fP=""
	Currency: aud|usd (required)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for checkout

.PP
\fB--success-url\fP=""
	URL Stripe redirects to after a successful payment (optional)

.PP
\fB--tier\fP=""
	Tier to subscribe to: payg|starter|pro|business|enterprise (required)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--api-url\fP=""
	API base URL (env: BCDOCK_API_URL)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format: table, json, csv

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--timeout\fP=30s
	Request timeout

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	API token (env: BCDOCK_TOKEN)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bcdock me billing checkout --tier starter --currency aud
  bcdock me billing checkout --tier pro --currency usd
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBbcdock-me-billing(1)\fP
